    "comment": "Rationale: Figure 1, 2, table 1: RAB11 was identified in biochemical enrichment of neuronal endosomes.\n\nFigure 5, 6: immunofluerescence imaging showed RAB11 co-localized with presynaptic marker proteins, constitutively active Rab11 (Rab11Q70L) was recruited to nerve terminals and facilitates activity-dependent bulk endocytosis.\n\nAuthors concluded that \"Rab11Q70L preferentially localizes to nerve terminals, as does endogenous Rab11 (SI Appendix, Fig. S13).\". Experimental description: supplemental M&M: \"Primary cultures of cerebellar granule neurons (CGNs) were prepared from the cerebella of 7 day old Sprague Dawley rat pups of both sexes as described\"\n\nto disambiguate \"Rab11\"; table 1 reports Rab11a (P62494), the streetname of Rab11a is Rab11",
